015package com.google.common.util.concurrent;
016
017import com.google.common.annotations.GwtIncompatible;
018import com.google.common.annotations.J2ktIncompatible;
019import com.google.errorprone.annotations.CanIgnoreReturnValue;
020import com.google.errorprone.annotations.CheckReturnValue;
021import java.util.concurrent.AbstractExecutorService;
022import java.util.concurrent.Callable;
023import java.util.concurrent.RunnableFuture;
024import org.jspecify.annotations.Nullable;
025
026/**
027 * Abstract {@link ListeningExecutorService} implementation that creates {@link ListenableFuture}
028 * instances for each {@link Runnable} and {@link Callable} submitted to it. These tasks are run
029 * with the abstract {@link #execute execute(Runnable)} method.
030 *
031 * <p>In addition to {@link #execute}, subclasses must implement all methods related to shutdown and
032 * termination.
033 *
034 * @author Chris Povirk
035 * @since 14.0
036 */
037@CheckReturnValue
038@GwtIncompatible
039@J2ktIncompatible
040public abstract class AbstractListeningExecutorService extends AbstractExecutorService
041    implements ListeningExecutorService {
042  /** Constructor for use by subclasses. */
043  public AbstractListeningExecutorService() {}
044
045  /**
046   * @since 19.0 (present with return type {@code ListenableFutureTask} since 14.0)
047   */
048  @CanIgnoreReturnValue // TODO(kak): consider removing this
049  @Override
050  protected final <T extends @Nullable Object> RunnableFuture<T> newTaskFor(
051      Runnable runnable, @ParametricNullness T value) {
052    return TrustedListenableFutureTask.create(runnable, value);
053  }
054
055  /**
056   * @since 19.0 (present with return type {@code ListenableFutureTask} since 14.0)
057   */
058  @CanIgnoreReturnValue // TODO(kak): consider removing this
059  @Override
060  protected final <T extends @Nullable Object> RunnableFuture<T> newTaskFor(Callable<T> callable) {
061    return TrustedListenableFutureTask.create(callable);
062  }
063
064  @CanIgnoreReturnValue // TODO(kak): consider removing this
065  @Override
066  public ListenableFuture<?> submit(Runnable task) {
067    return (ListenableFuture<?>) super.submit(task);
068  }
069
070  @CanIgnoreReturnValue // TODO(kak): consider removing this
071  @Override
072  public <T extends @Nullable Object> ListenableFuture<T> submit(
073      Runnable task, @ParametricNullness T result) {
074    return (ListenableFuture<T>) super.submit(task, result);
075  }
076
077  @CanIgnoreReturnValue // TODO(kak): consider removing this
078  @Override
079  public <T extends @Nullable Object> ListenableFuture<T> submit(Callable<T> task) {
080    return (ListenableFuture<T>) super.submit(task);
081  }
082}
